⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Crime
node CPS · CPS · ⟦The Crime:CPS:433e93⟧

WHO   — The Crime — the killing of the stepfather
WHAT  — The act moved from philosophy to revenge: a killing the audience is invited to half-understand, which is precisely what the novel refuses.
WHERE — CPS · Crime + Punishment in Suburbia  Framework inputs: Crime + Punishment in Suburbia (2000)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because by making the crime sympathetic the film changes the question from ‘can reason excuse murder?’ to ‘can love forgive it?’
HOW   — By a desperate teenage act after the stepfather's final cruelty.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the axe, transposed — but I fell on an abuser, not a harmless old woman, and that swing changed the whole meaning of the blow.

